summary: As requested, notes from the public lecture: The Cost of Destroying a Death Star (or 2)  Rewritten note from yesterday's lecture...
body:
As requested, notes from the public lecture: The Cost of Destroying a Death Star (or 2)

Rewritten note from yesterday’s lecture because I could barely read my scribbles in light grey. I couldn’t get a hold of the keynote, but here is a link (PDF) to the paper Prof. Feinstein wrote, on which the lecture was based on. I might have jotted down some numbers too quickly, so the paper definitely has the right ones. The lecture itself was full of (bad) puns, and 95% were there for Star Wars (5%, including me, were there for the maths and Star Wars). I really love my uni sometimes.

@athenastudying @coffeeandpies there you go my fellow Star Wars nerds!

and you too @a-cat-studying , goodness how could I forget!

summary: These teasing bastards! Anyway, besides the thank you card, we have to jars here - one filled with sand and the other filled...
caption:
These teasing bastards!

Anyway, besides the thank you card, we have to jars here - one filled with sand and the other filled with rocks(?). The sand jar says, “from a long time ago, not so far away,” and the other jar says, “swallowing you up whole!!!”

The sand jar could mean we’re returning to Jakku or Tatooine (or simply an “I don’t like sand” joke). The other jar’s quote makes me think about the Sarlacc Pit from Return of the Jedi because the Sarlacc swallowed people whole. 

Who knows what this mean! We’ll find out eventually.

No nonsense publishing editor hard business woman thirty nine year old divorcee Rey Philips in too busy and practical for her friend rose Ticos nonsense. But rose kept trying to tell her to move on. Plus her mother Kira not understanding why She suddenly divorced her husband. Rey not having the heart to tell her mother. Only her dad knowing. One day rose books a flight to Hawaii forcing rey to take a two week vacation from work. While there she meets sexy young twenty three year old waiter and bar tender Kylo Ren who rey is determined to stay far away from the man is far to young for her but he has other ideas.

summary:
Star Wars Adventures: Destroyer Down #3 Publisher: IDW Publishing 

(W) Scott Beatty (A) Jon Sommariva (A/CA) Derek Charm...
caption:
Star Wars Adventures: Destroyer Down #3

Publisher: IDW Publishing
(W) Scott Beatty (A) Jon Sommariva (A/CA) Derek Charm

Swallowed by the shifting sands of Jakku, the Imperial Star Destroyer Spectral has been lost for two decades, giving rise to rumors of hauntings and buried treasure. But an epic sandstorm has revealed the ruins of the starship, and renowned scavenger Rey now leads the race to claim whatever lies within!

Three-issue miniseries set during the days before The Force Awakens!
Includes a backup story depicting the Battle of Jakku, revealing how the Star Destroyer Spectral met its fate during the last days of the Empire!

In Shops: Jan 09, 2019

Adventures in fandom and creative writing

Here, you'll find a lot of fandom-related posts...and a heck of a lot of writing. So much writing. I do writing prompts just about every weekday, Monday to Friday.

What you're not going to find are posts that insult others or put people down. There's enough of that in the real world: I don't need any on my blog, thanks.

tags: lol i basically just rewrote the opening crawl seuss style
body:
Fic Prompts: Star Wars Wednesday

(Return of the Seussified Jedi!)

A Long Time Ago, In A Galaxy Far, Far Away…

The Death Star’s destroyed, and hope lights a spark-

But for the Rebellion it’s a time that is dark!

The Empire’s forces had found their abode,

So they’ve packed up their things and they’ve gone on the road.

Past asteroids!

Past planets!

To danger they’ll go,

Til Luke and his friends find a world made of snow!

A place they can hide where the Empire won’t know!

But out in the stars, far from snow, ice, and sleet,

Sits the pride of the dreadful Imperial Fleet!

Who brings this ship out here, this vast monolith?

The Executor’s master: Darth Vader the Sith!

He searches for Luke, and he won’t be denied:

He’ll trace him to any world where he could hide.

“I’ll find him by Force,

If only a trace!

I’ll find him with probe droids

I’ve launched into space!

On planets, on asteroids, on starships and moons-

In oceans, in jungles, in sand or snow dunes.

I’ll find him, whatever means I must employ.

I have to track down this rebellious boy!”

And so Vader said, for so Vader meant.

For a Sith lord is stubborn, one hundred percent.

summary: GRYFFINDOR: "He stood as viceroy of Alderaan at the beginning of a dark time for our galaxy. He helped Mon Mothma create the...
caption: GRYFFINDOR: “He stood as viceroy of Alderaan at the beginning of a dark time for our galaxy. He helped Mon Mothma create the Rebel Alliance, even while still fighting valiantly to preserve what little integrity and authority the Imperial Senate had left. I have no doubt that he would have continued to battle alongside our rebel soldiers if he had not so cruelly been taken from us in the destruction of my homeworld.” –Claudia Gray (Leia Organa: Star Wars: Bloodline)
